external_knowledge:
- 'Instruments that light the way' refers to the sensors whose detailed information is being sought. ; 
- 'Characteristics' covers the parameters, conditions, units, and performance specifications. ; 
- 'Facets of their measurements' include the minimum, typical, and maximum values of the parameters. ; 
- 'Borders of their operational ranges' refer to the min_value and max_value columns. ; 
- 'Version' in the metaphorical sense can be thought of as the iteration or specification version number of the sensor's performance. ; 
- 'Time-stamped with their introduction and last acquaintance' refers to the upload_date and access_date, which indicate when the sensor data was first recorded and last accessed.

- 'compass needles' refers to magnetometers;
- 'magnetic sea' refers to the operational environment of magnetometers;
- 'whispers' refer to measurements of 'Dynamic Range';
- 'microteslas' are the units measured in 'uT'.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM sensors
WHERE sensor_id = 1;

SELECT sensors.sensor_name, parameters.parameter_name
FROM sensors
JOIN parameters ON sensors.sensor_id = parameters.sensor_id;

SELECT sensor_id, sensor_name, description, sensor_type, manufacturer, model_number, serial_number, calibration_date
FROM sensors
WHERE manufacturer LIKE 'Manufacturer%' AND sensor_id IN (1, 2);
